And then this Mampara, acting through his lackeys, wipes out R50-billion by charging his finance minister over a matter many deem administrative.In the same week that his stooges argue for Pravin Gordhan to be hauled before court because "no one is above the law", this Mampara rushes to the court to stop the release of a report that might show him dancing to the tune of his friends, the Guptas.If he believes in the rule of law, this Mampara of a president would withdraw his latest legal attempt to stop the reinstatement of the corruption case against him.